This paper discusses the support for data feed ingestion in a Big Data Management System (BDMS), which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the challenges and implementation of managing data feeds, which involves concepts related to data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the customization of resources and robustness for high-level applications, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses scalability and fault-tolerance, which are topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
